SIMPLE: orle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orle
<hw>Orle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>orle</ets> an
orle, a fillet, fr. LL. <ets>orla</ets> border, dim. of L.
<ets>ora</ets> border, margin.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>A bearing, in the form of a
fillet, round the shield, within, but at some distance from, the
border.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>The wreath, or chaplet,
surmounting or encircling the helmet of a knight and bearing the
crest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>In orle</b></col>, <cd>round the escutcheon, leaving the
middle of the field vacant, or occupied by something else; -- said of
bearings arranged on the shield in the form of an orle.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orleans</ent>⟦br⟧
